Do you think, or what are your thoughts on the quality
of officer training that you're receiving?
Well, I've had many, many social conversations and many, many more conversations with
contemporaries as well as seniors from West Point.
I wouldn't in any way try to say that that at A&M was better than VMI because VMI are faced with the same problems that people at A&M are faced with.
The quality of training for me is so much better at A&M and BMI than at one of the military schools because
One of the military academies?
One of the military academies.
West Point, Annapolis, or even the Air Force Academy.
Because to start with, the beginner didn't get there by being hand-selected and therefore have the feeling that
I am something just by being human.
He still has to win his first and he still has a chance of being the top guy or he can end up right on the bottom.
He is not assured that if he graduates that he's going to have any type of a career, which
therefore doesn't build into him any type of complacency.
He has a more awkward look on life and the way life is lived and even business and economy.
You don't have just blinders on that says, let's take one of the schools, Westmont, I want to name it.

Everybody takes the same course, no matter whether you came there with two years, three years, or were already a graduate from another college or what, and you take this course, and when you finish, you're a second lieutenant.
Now, according to rank in the class, you can decide what you want to go into.
The infantry, the engineers, or the artillery, or what do you want to go into?
And you get your pick, according to so many down the line.
They say, well, that's what they're supposed to do, but I don't fully agree.
They have educated this man to do one thing, and that's to serve in the army.
Unfortunately, when the guy gets to a certain level, and he gets there in a hurry, he's got to deal with too many people that are not subject to military discipline.
That's civil servants.
And he's got to deal with business people to see that he's getting the best deal that he can for the Army or for his unit.
And it's just not there.
And so you think at West Point they just don't have that training, but they do at A&M?
Certainly.

I was done.
